Conclusions: Objectively measured neighborhood and route factors are associated with walking and cycling to school. However, distance did not moderate the associations found here. Creating safe environments by improving urban design may influence children’s commuting behavior. Intervention studies are needed to confırm the fındings from this observational cross-sectional study.},
